1
00:00:34,233 --> 00:00:36,557
Look into my eyes.

2
00:00:40,515 --> 00:00:43,349
There's no fear. There's only light.

3
00:00:48,399 --> 00:00:51,275
I am the light.

4
00:01:05,859 --> 00:01:08,691
The light is me.

5
00:01:21,985 --> 00:01:24,944
There's no fear.

6
00:01:25,111 --> 00:01:27,902
There's only light.

7
00:01:37,486 --> 00:01:40,111
Only light.

8
00:02:31,195 --> 00:02:35,527
- That's him, in the uniform.
- Thanks.

9
00:02:39,570 --> 00:02:42,611
Christian Habersaat?

10
00:02:42,777 --> 00:02:48,361
Sorry for barging in like this.
I didn't know you were retiring today.

11
00:02:48,527 --> 00:02:54,236
- I'm being forced to retire.
- I'm sorry to hear that.

12
00:02:54,402 --> 00:02:58,069
I'm Rose Knudsen.
I was sent here to speak to you.

13
00:02:58,236 --> 00:03:04,377
- About what?
- From Department Q? Carl sent me.

14
00:03:04,378 --> 00:03:08,195
I've tried to reach Carl
for three months.

15
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:13,069
- Now he sends his assistant...
- I'm not his assistant.

16
00:03:13,236 --> 00:03:17,527
- I'm a detective.
- I'm afraid you're too late.

17
00:03:22,819 --> 00:03:27,069
I promise to make this brief,
because there's one thing I know:

18
00:03:27,235 --> 00:03:33,611
People would rather drink than listen
to a bitter retiring policeman like me.

19
00:03:33,777 --> 00:03:37,945
So here's what I want to say to you.

20
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:41,235
Figure out what motivates you.

21
00:03:42,694 --> 00:03:46,444
Is it conscience? Necessity?

22
00:03:47,945 --> 00:03:50,402
Is it loyalty?

23
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:54,985
Thoroughness?

24
00:03:55,153 --> 00:03:57,652
What do you say, Bak?

25
00:03:58,902 --> 00:04:04,110
Well, I suppose it's all of the above.
But let's say cheers to that.

26
00:04:04,278 --> 00:04:08,319
With the risk of sounding
somewhat lofty...

27
00:04:08,486 --> 00:04:12,070
I believe in justice.

28
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:16,110
Christian... Stop.

29
00:04:16,278 --> 00:04:18,528
Stop!

30
00:04:21,985 --> 00:04:24,778
Tell them to put down their weapons.

31
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:32,069
- Right now.
- Do as he says. Put down your guns.

32
00:04:34,444 --> 00:04:37,486
Get the camera.

33
00:04:43,194 --> 00:04:46,320
Come here. Closer.

34
00:04:46,485 --> 00:04:48,820
Christian, listen. Stop it.

35
00:04:55,986 --> 00:04:58,986
Christian?

36
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:12,320
BOUNDLESS

37
00:05:15,195 --> 00:05:18,944
INCOMING CALL
ROSE KNUDSEN

38
00:05:19,111 --> 00:05:22,778
DEAR MONA
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

39
00:05:22,944 --> 00:05:27,278
- It's Carl.
- He shot himself.

40
00:05:27,444 --> 00:05:30,861
Christian Habersaat. At his reception.

41
00:05:34,695 --> 00:05:40,444
- Bloody hell. Were you there?
- Of course I was. You told me to go.

42
00:05:40,611 --> 00:05:46,985
- You shouldn't be there. Come home.
- I want to stay for the funeral.

43
00:05:47,153 --> 00:05:52,945
- For his funeral?
- Carl, he shot himself in front of me.

44
00:05:54,028 --> 00:05:58,528
- I understand.
- What's this about, Carl?

45
00:05:58,694 --> 00:06:03,778
- He'd written your name inside his hand.
- My name on his hand?

46
00:06:03,944 --> 00:06:08,152
- Why the hell did he do that?
- I assumed you could tell me.

47
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:13,236
- How the hell should I know?
- You've got to come here, Carl.

48
00:06:15,194 --> 00:06:18,277
- What's up?
- I have to go to Bornholm.

49
00:06:21,402 --> 00:06:26,610
Good thing you called.
Tell me about Christian Habersaat.

50
00:06:26,778 --> 00:06:29,235
Well...

51
00:06:29,403 --> 00:06:32,986
The man was depressed.
He wasn't right in the head.

52
00:06:33,152 --> 00:06:38,110
He spent the past seven years on some
case about a girl found dead in a tree.

53
00:06:38,278 --> 00:06:44,235
The Alberte Schneider case.
They mentioned it yesterday.

54
00:06:44,403 --> 00:06:49,152
A nasty affair. She was only 21.
They closed the case.

55
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:53,110
- Murdered in traffic.
- You mean a hit-and-run?

56
00:06:53,277 --> 00:06:57,194
Yes, apparently.
But Habersaat couldn't let it go.

57
00:06:57,361 --> 00:06:59,986
Things went downhill from there.

58
00:07:00,152 --> 00:07:04,570
The case became an obsession for him.

59
00:07:04,735 --> 00:07:09,902
He stops sleeping. He gets weird.
Friends and colleagues get fed up.

60
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:13,320
Finally his wife leaves him,
and all that's left is work.

61
00:07:13,485 --> 00:07:18,528
You'll pick me up, right? I won't stay
on that island longer than I have to.

62
00:07:22,069 --> 00:07:26,527
- He was your friend, wasn't he?
- I wouldn't call it that.

63
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:30,028
We attended the police academy together.

64
00:07:30,194 --> 00:07:34,528
Me and Christian, Hardy, Bak.
The police commissioner here.

65
00:07:34,694 --> 00:07:40,485
- What was he like? Christian?
- He was a good guy.

66
00:07:40,653 --> 00:07:45,735
I haven't seen him for years, so it was
strange when he started calling.

67
00:07:45,903 --> 00:07:49,402
He called you for three months,
and you never called back.

68
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:53,652
I know, and I feel bad about it now.
I should have.

69
00:07:53,819 --> 00:07:58,361
- You didn't want to speak to him.
- Yes, I did. Shut up now.

70
00:08:05,486 --> 00:08:08,403
He looked like my dad.

71
00:08:08,569 --> 00:08:11,735
Christian Habersaat?
He did?

72
00:08:14,069 --> 00:08:18,528
It's intense,
seeing a person shoot themselves.

73
00:08:18,694 --> 00:08:24,110
- How's... that thing going?
- That thing?

74
00:08:25,236 --> 00:08:28,694
Yeah, your dad thing.

75
00:08:28,861 --> 00:08:31,236
My dad thing?

76
00:08:36,569 --> 00:08:40,028
Blessed be the God and Father
of our Lord Jesus Christ -

77
00:08:40,194 --> 00:08:44,360
- who according to His mercy
has caused us to be born again -

78
00:08:44,528 --> 00:08:48,403
- through the resurrection of Jesus
Christ from the dead...

79
00:08:51,860 --> 00:08:56,861
Christian Habersaat,
from dust you came...

80
00:09:00,985 --> 00:09:03,819
to dust you shall return.

81
00:09:08,402 --> 00:09:11,195
From dust you shall arise.

82
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:16,361
Figure out what motivates you.
Is it conscience? Necessity?

83
00:09:17,860 --> 00:09:20,570
I saw him the day before.
He was fine then.

84
00:09:20,735 --> 00:09:23,735
He was disappointed, though,
that you were ignoring his calls.

85
00:09:23,903 --> 00:09:27,528
You think he shot himself
just to get Carl over here?

86
00:09:27,694 --> 00:09:31,902
- What would he want to talk to me about?
- The Alberte Schneider case.

87
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:34,320
What? Nonsense.

88
00:09:34,485 --> 00:09:38,360
For Christian,
everything was about Alberte Schneider.

89
00:09:38,528 --> 00:09:44,028
- So that case really fucked him up?
- It fucked up the whole island.

90
00:09:51,152 --> 00:09:54,778
When Bak closed the case,
Christian took it all home.

91
00:09:54,944 --> 00:09:59,986
I think you should go by his house and
have a look. He would've appreciated it.

92
00:10:02,194 --> 00:10:03,777
Carl?

93
00:10:03,945 --> 00:10:07,069
- Long time, no see.
- You're so right.

94
00:10:08,985 --> 00:10:12,819
Yep, it's a mess.
I guess I should have seen it coming.

95
00:10:12,986 --> 00:10:16,653
- Seen what coming?
- Would you mind introducing us?

96
00:10:16,819 --> 00:10:19,652
This is Rose, Department Q.
Henrik Bak.

97
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:23,111
- Rose Knudsen.
- Police Commissioner Henrik Bak.

98
00:10:23,277 --> 00:10:26,610
We went
to the police academy together, so, uh...

99
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:32,278
It's funny,
we used to call him Pussy-Carl.

100
00:10:32,444 --> 00:10:36,944
But Christian,
he was a good police officer.

101
00:10:37,111 --> 00:10:42,403
- Right until Alberte got in the way.
- In the way? Of what?

102
00:10:42,569 --> 00:10:47,069
- Of his work, or...?
- 250 people die in traffic each year.

103
00:10:47,236 --> 00:10:49,861
You don't have to build a space rocket
every time.

104
00:10:50,027 --> 00:10:52,860
So, no reason for you to stick around.

105
00:10:53,028 --> 00:10:55,986
You didn't tell me
he'd written my name in his hand.

106
00:10:56,152 --> 00:10:58,337
Not the first time
a suicide victim addresses his motive.

107
00:10:58,361 --> 00:11:03,903
You're saying I'm his motive?
I thought it was Alberte Schneider.

108
00:11:04,069 --> 00:11:09,235
As far as I remember, Christian had
plenty of reason to hate you.

109
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:13,195
- Are you being serious?
- Yes, I am.

110
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:18,944
- Bak, you bloody idiot.
- That's typical you. Always smarter.

111
00:11:19,111 --> 00:11:22,860
It was like that at the academy, too.
Everyone looked up to you.

112
00:11:23,028 --> 00:11:26,152
They looked up to me?
You must be mistaken.

113
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:30,778
It was always like: "Carl, Carl, Carl."
"Carl will make it big-time."

114
00:11:30,944 --> 00:11:35,403
Yet here I am: Chief Commissioner.
And you?

115
00:11:36,736 --> 00:11:39,986
What are you exactly, Carl?

116
00:11:40,152 --> 00:11:44,985
- What the hell are we talking about?
- I'm saying that you should go home.

117
00:11:45,153 --> 00:11:48,194
And take your assistant with you.

118
00:11:51,569 --> 00:11:56,486
- You're the dumbest person I know.
- Goodbye, Carl.

119
00:11:56,652 --> 00:11:58,861
Fucking jerk.

120
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:02,820
- Did we get the house key?
- Yes.

121
00:12:02,985 --> 00:12:05,070
Then let's go.

122
00:12:36,444 --> 00:12:40,778
Now this is a renovation project
that came to a halt.

123
00:12:42,944 --> 00:12:46,485
THE ALBERTE SCHNEIDER CASE
SHUT DOWN

124
00:13:03,485 --> 00:13:06,486
Carl, come here for a second.

125
00:13:10,235 --> 00:13:13,986
- What the hell is this picture?
- Holy shit.

126
00:13:15,278 --> 00:13:19,861
It must be a forensic image
that's been digitally manipulated.

127
00:13:20,027 --> 00:13:23,445
- Is that her?
- Alberte? I guess so.

128
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:26,610
Jesus, the guy was religious about it.

129
00:13:52,902 --> 00:13:55,403
Carl?

130
00:13:55,569 --> 00:13:58,361
Someone's in the house.

131
00:14:08,653 --> 00:14:10,819
Hello?

132
00:14:20,403 --> 00:14:22,485
Fuck!

133
00:14:24,278 --> 00:14:28,820
Hey. Hey! Are you with me?
Hey, look at me!

134
00:14:30,027 --> 00:14:33,528
Hey. What's your name?

135
00:14:36,819 --> 00:14:40,570
Christ!
Goddammit...

136
00:14:40,735 --> 00:14:44,069
- Has he got a pulse?
- No pulse.

137
00:14:50,194 --> 00:14:52,903
Copenhagen Police.
We need an ambulance.

138
00:14:53,069 --> 00:14:57,486
- A young man in his 20s has OD'ed.
- Come on!

139
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:06,860
I'M SORRY DAD

140
00:15:07,028 --> 00:15:09,986
He's dead.

141
00:15:11,611 --> 00:15:14,694
It's Bjarke, Habersaat's only son.

142
00:15:14,861 --> 00:15:19,695
A sad fate who's been in and out
of rehab since he was a teenager.

143
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:24,444
- Who is his mother?
- June Habersaat, Christian's ex-wife.

144
00:15:24,611 --> 00:15:27,236
She was at the funeral too.

145
00:15:27,402 --> 00:15:31,819
Why write "I'm sorry" to your dad
who's been dead for days?

146
00:15:31,986 --> 00:15:34,860
- Birkedal?
- Coming. Thanks.

147
00:15:38,735 --> 00:15:45,194
- Let's get back to Copenhagen.
- We can't go to Copenhagen now.

148
00:15:46,527 --> 00:15:51,278
Habersaat tried to get you
to look at this case for months.

149
00:15:51,444 --> 00:15:54,069
It's not our job. I think
we can make the 9 PM departure.

150
00:15:54,236 --> 00:15:59,194
Or we could grab some food first,
and take the late ferry. You coming?

151
00:15:59,361 --> 00:16:01,444
Carl.

152
00:16:08,027 --> 00:16:11,070
Why are you stopping here?

153
00:16:11,235 --> 00:16:14,152
- I'm staying.
- What do you mean?

154
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:18,195
- There's a case here.
- No, you're coming home with me.

155
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:21,486
Otherwise
there are grounds for dismissal.

156
00:16:21,652 --> 00:16:24,027
- You're firing me?
- Yes.

157
00:16:24,195 --> 00:16:26,485
I mean... yes.

158
00:16:28,110 --> 00:16:32,528
Oh, come on.
Get the fuck out of the car, Carl.

159
00:16:32,694 --> 00:16:38,070
It's your mess to deal with.
Don't call me. I won't pick up.

160
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:41,903
Hi, Carl.

161
00:17:42,069 --> 00:17:46,111
- Assad? What are you doing here?
- Rose called, so I took the last ferry.

162
00:17:46,277 --> 00:17:48,736
- She told me what it's about.
- I don't even know it's about.

163
00:17:48,902 --> 00:17:53,444
That's why she called me.
She thinks you're an idiot.

164
00:17:53,611 --> 00:17:57,278
- Have you got a single or double bed?
- You're not sleeping here.

165
00:17:57,444 --> 00:18:01,652
Everything's booked.
That's why they gave you the basement.

166
00:18:01,820 --> 00:18:06,569
- I'm a heavy sleeper.
- Sleep heavily in the car. Goodnight.

167
00:18:06,736 --> 00:18:08,903
Carl.

168
00:18:24,735 --> 00:18:29,319
I've had it. Assad! Assad!
Hey, Assad!

169
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:39,195
Argh, goddammit!

170
00:18:40,195 --> 00:18:43,860
- For Christ's sake.
- What's up, Carl?

171
00:18:44,028 --> 00:18:49,320
- What the hell? You're out here?
- I like sleeping outside.

172
00:18:49,485 --> 00:18:52,444
Yeah, it is nice.

173
00:18:52,611 --> 00:18:56,027
What's up with that Bak?
Did you fuck his wife?

174
00:18:56,195 --> 00:19:01,235
God, no. I sure as hell haven't.
I don't think he even has.

175
00:19:01,403 --> 00:19:04,278
But you and Habersaat
were good friends?

176
00:19:04,444 --> 00:19:08,236
Yes, we were pretty close.

177
00:19:08,402 --> 00:19:11,610
Rowdy young guys,
driving around, drinking beers.

178
00:19:11,778 --> 00:19:15,902
Then what happened between you?

179
00:19:16,069 --> 00:19:19,360
Oh, you know, we just drifted apart.

180
00:19:19,528 --> 00:19:22,944
Christian got one of the local
girls pregnant and stuck around.

181
00:19:23,111 --> 00:19:26,902
- Was it that woman, June?
- Yes.

182
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:29,611
June.

183
00:19:29,777 --> 00:19:34,985
And Bjarke was their kid?
Wasn't that thirty years ago?

184
00:19:35,153 --> 00:19:39,403
Yeah. Yes, I guess it was.

185
00:19:39,569 --> 00:19:42,695
- Did you know her?
- What?

186
00:19:42,860 --> 00:19:45,861
Did you know her? June?

187
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:58,402
Rose, you know what?
Let's do it. Let's stay.

188
00:19:58,570 --> 00:20:01,945
But we'll run things without Bak.
We'll do it our way.

189
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:04,277
Good decision.

190
00:20:04,445 --> 00:20:06,695
Pussy-Carl.

191
00:20:24,278 --> 00:20:27,278
Feel the light on you.

192
00:20:30,153 --> 00:20:34,486
- I feel the light.
- I feel the light.

193
00:20:34,652 --> 00:20:38,860
- The light is strength.
- Light is strength.

194
00:20:39,860 --> 00:20:42,278
Good, Wanda.

195
00:20:51,361 --> 00:20:55,027
How the hell did she end up
all the way up there?

196
00:20:55,195 --> 00:21:00,652
The report supposes she's biking along,
gets hit, flips over in the air -

197
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:04,028
- and lands on that branch.

198
00:21:04,194 --> 00:21:08,735
Calculations prove it's possible
if the car was driving fast enough.

199
00:21:08,903 --> 00:21:11,985
Of course.
They are all idiots.

200
00:21:13,445 --> 00:21:18,403
We know she was seen taking off
at 5:15 AM on her red bike.

201
00:21:20,653 --> 00:21:25,195
- Why bike here at the crack of dawn?
- Does the report say anything?

202
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:30,610
It supposes she was going swimming
off a cliff down that road.

203
00:21:30,778 --> 00:21:35,278
Let me get this straight.
She's hit over there, smack, flies up -

204
00:21:35,444 --> 00:21:38,528
- lands on the branch.

205
00:21:40,069 --> 00:21:45,111
They send tyre tracks to every mechanic
on the island...

206
00:23:10,152 --> 00:23:13,110
Let's get started.

207
00:23:13,278 --> 00:23:17,402
I brought some things from Habersaat's.
We need to go collect more.

208
00:23:17,570 --> 00:23:20,860
I'm going to the folk high school
to ask about Alberte.

209
00:23:21,028 --> 00:23:23,527
- I'll come with you.
- Let's go.

210
00:23:23,695 --> 00:23:27,819
- I've got some business here...
- See you.

211
00:23:44,944 --> 00:23:48,277
Our principal is at a meeting
of the island. Can I help you?

212
00:23:48,445 --> 00:23:51,235
Rose Knudsen, Copenhagen Police.

213
00:23:51,403 --> 00:23:55,819
- Simon Fabian. I'm the concierge here.
- Assad. Detective.

214
00:23:55,986 --> 00:23:58,778
- You mean caretaker, in Danish?
- Exactly.

215
00:23:58,944 --> 00:24:03,986
- How long have you worked here?
- Nearly 11 years.

216
00:24:04,152 --> 00:24:07,444
So you were here
when Alberte Schneider attended?

217
00:24:07,611 --> 00:24:13,445
- Did you know her?
- I strive to know all our students.

218
00:24:13,610 --> 00:24:16,070
- Why?
- So I can better help them.

219
00:24:16,235 --> 00:24:22,402
It's hard being young. A place like this
is full of temptation, you know?

220
00:24:23,819 --> 00:24:26,903
Okay, can you show us her old room?

221
00:24:27,069 --> 00:24:30,985
This was her room.
But she moved out prematurely.

222
00:24:31,152 --> 00:24:35,320
- What was on the walls?
- Her own things, mostly.

223
00:24:35,485 --> 00:24:38,735
She was constantly drawing.

224
00:24:38,903 --> 00:24:42,360
At first, she loved drawing animals...

225
00:24:42,528 --> 00:24:46,152
Especially dead ones.
Talented. Very ambitious...

226
00:24:47,653 --> 00:24:50,485
It was very gloomy.

227
00:24:53,611 --> 00:24:58,235
Over time, it became lighter,
more spiritual.

228
00:24:59,902 --> 00:25:04,735
- You seem to know a lot about art.
- I've picked up a thing or two.

229
00:25:04,903 --> 00:25:08,027
I collected all her things in a box
when emptying her room.

230
00:25:08,195 --> 00:25:13,485
- May we take a look?
- Sure. I'd like to ask her family first.

231
00:25:13,653 --> 00:25:17,986
- Did she date anyone?
- She was somewhat exclusive.

232
00:25:18,152 --> 00:25:22,735
Just a few. She preferred them older,
as far as I remember.

233
00:25:22,903 --> 00:25:27,485
- Anyone in particular?
- I couldn't say, Rose.

234
00:25:27,653 --> 00:25:30,735
That would be disloyal, wouldn't it?

235
00:25:30,903 --> 00:25:36,570
- Disloyal to whom?
- Alberte, of course.

236
00:25:36,735 --> 00:25:41,653
- Thanks. We'll just take a look around.
- Let me know if I can help.

237
00:25:41,819 --> 00:25:46,986
My workshop's in the basement.
Feel free to stop by if you need me.

238
00:25:51,610 --> 00:25:55,152
- Fucking idiot.
- He just thought you were hot.

239
00:25:58,485 --> 00:26:01,985
- Should we listen to the lecture?
- I have to pick up Carl.

240
00:26:04,277 --> 00:26:08,736
Come get me afterwards.
I'm going to speak to some people.

241
00:26:08,902 --> 00:26:12,236
Continue swaying softly...

242
00:26:15,694 --> 00:26:19,486
Press your palms against
your neighbour's.

243
00:26:22,111 --> 00:26:26,069
Turn your faces towards the light.

244
00:26:29,611 --> 00:26:37,320
Feel how the light and heat spreads
through your body.

245
00:26:42,236 --> 00:26:45,069
Feel the heat.

246
00:26:47,445 --> 00:26:51,902
Do you feel the unique energy
that arises between you?

247
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:55,110
Yes!

248
00:26:55,278 --> 00:27:01,111
Good.
This is what our community is all about.

249
00:27:01,277 --> 00:27:07,485
We capture this energy,
so you can find a path to yourself.

250
00:27:07,653 --> 00:27:13,445
Find out who you were before you let
others decide a direction for you.

251
00:27:18,695 --> 00:27:21,653
Does it feel good?

252
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:41,486
- Hi, June.
- What do you want?

253
00:27:41,652 --> 00:27:45,485
I saw you at the funeral.

254
00:27:45,653 --> 00:27:49,028
Can we talk?

255
00:27:49,194 --> 00:27:51,735
Come around back.

256
00:27:59,569 --> 00:28:02,070
So, what is it you want?

257
00:28:08,402 --> 00:28:11,569
Are you okay?

258
00:28:11,736 --> 00:28:16,903
Am I okay? Okay with my son just dying?

259
00:28:17,069 --> 00:28:19,694
Or okay with you being here?

260
00:28:22,652 --> 00:28:26,403
I was the one who found Bjarke.

261
00:28:26,569 --> 00:28:29,695
I'm so sorry.

262
00:28:29,860 --> 00:28:34,027
He was... He was a really fine boy.

263
00:28:41,695 --> 00:28:46,653
But that's why you're here, right?
To ask about Bjarke?

264
00:28:48,069 --> 00:28:52,319
- Why do you think that?
- You know why.

265
00:28:55,986 --> 00:28:58,069
Um...

266
00:29:02,027 --> 00:29:05,778
Bjarke was...
Bjarke was your son.

267
00:29:24,110 --> 00:29:27,236
- Bjarke was my son?
- Yes.

268
00:29:28,735 --> 00:29:31,236
You know that.

269
00:29:32,528 --> 00:29:35,319
How the hell could I know that?

270
00:29:36,445 --> 00:29:39,653
What the hell? You can't just say that.

271
00:29:40,860 --> 00:29:46,694
We had an agreement. You would have
it removed. We discussed it.

272
00:29:46,861 --> 00:29:50,736
Yes, we discussed it,
and then you disappeared.

273
00:29:51,986 --> 00:29:55,819
I wouldn't say "disappeared".
Why didn't you call me?

274
00:29:55,986 --> 00:30:01,027
Would it have made any difference?
Would you have come back to play family?

275
00:30:01,195 --> 00:30:06,070
That's not the point.
Maybe I would have.

276
00:30:06,235 --> 00:30:09,278
This is madness.
It's not okay, June.

277
00:30:09,444 --> 00:30:13,570
- I'm about to get married.
- Well, congratulations.

278
00:30:13,735 --> 00:30:15,985
June!

279
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,402
June.

280
00:30:22,735 --> 00:30:24,694
June.

281
00:30:25,903 --> 00:30:30,985
All our stories and traumas
create holes inside us.

282
00:30:31,153 --> 00:30:35,194
And if we don't deal with them
and take responsibility -

283
00:30:35,361 --> 00:30:39,652
- they become powerful enough
to ruin our lives.

284
00:30:41,570 --> 00:30:44,361
But we don't want that.

285
00:30:44,527 --> 00:30:48,403
We want to fill them with light.
Light and love.

286
00:30:48,570 --> 00:30:53,778
So ask yourselves:
What is my story?

287
00:30:53,944 --> 00:30:57,111
And will I let it ruin my life?

288
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:06,528
Thank you for listening
I know it was long.

289
00:31:06,694 --> 00:31:11,610
Thank you for coming.
Thanks to the school for hosting us.

290
00:31:16,444 --> 00:31:20,027
Did you like what you heard?

291
00:31:20,195 --> 00:31:23,985
Yes. It was... yes.

292
00:31:25,194 --> 00:31:29,028
- Good. What's your name?
- I'm Rose.

293
00:31:29,194 --> 00:31:31,611
Rose.

294
00:31:31,777 --> 00:31:34,945
I'll leave you in peace to absorb.

295
00:31:36,610 --> 00:31:40,361
- Absorb what?
- The light.

296
00:31:42,194 --> 00:31:45,735
- Oh, right.
- But...

297
00:31:45,903 --> 00:31:48,236
You're welcome to stop by sometime.

298
00:32:25,819 --> 00:32:28,444
So, finally you stopped by.

299
00:32:30,652 --> 00:32:35,986
- Bjarke's dead.
- Yeah. A pity, eh?

300
00:32:38,653 --> 00:32:40,611
Was he really my son?

301
00:32:40,777 --> 00:32:43,611
- Says who?
- June.

302
00:32:46,195 --> 00:32:50,111
So, again you come
to her little sister for gossip?

303
00:32:51,277 --> 00:32:56,653
Except I'm not in love with you anymore,
so you don't have much to bargain with.

304
00:32:56,820 --> 00:32:58,903
Fuck off.

305
00:33:04,361 --> 00:33:07,777
Come closer, goddammit,
and I'll tell you what I know.

306
00:33:15,027 --> 00:33:17,944
I know... that Bjarke...

307
00:33:20,736 --> 00:33:23,152
was yours!

308
00:33:28,610 --> 00:33:32,194
It was that bitch Alberte
who killed him.

309
00:33:33,860 --> 00:33:38,152
Alberte killed him?
But she's been dead for five years.

310
00:33:38,319 --> 00:33:40,944
They go swimming every morning
at dawn.

311
00:33:41,111 --> 00:33:43,153
Are you talking about Bjarke?

312
00:33:43,319 --> 00:33:47,485
No, Bjarke's scared of dead animals.
He's scared of everything.

313
00:33:47,653 --> 00:33:50,945
He's weird, but this guy...

314
00:33:52,278 --> 00:33:56,153
You can't tell by looking at him.
But he's frightening.

315
00:34:05,069 --> 00:34:07,903
And he wants her so badly.

316
00:34:08,069 --> 00:34:11,652
What's his name?
Who the hell are you talking about?

317
00:34:16,444 --> 00:34:20,319
You need to go, Carl. You can't be here.

318
00:34:20,486 --> 00:34:23,195
Get out of here!

319
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:25,445
Leave!

320
00:35:11,527 --> 00:35:15,486
Oh, it's you, stupid dog!
You want a beating?

321
00:35:15,652 --> 00:35:17,735
Scram.

322
00:35:24,444 --> 00:35:28,320
I didn't say anything!

323
00:35:55,861 --> 00:35:58,360
Hello?

324
00:36:14,569 --> 00:36:18,028
Beautiful weapon, eh?

325
00:36:19,902 --> 00:36:23,986
- I came to see Alberte's things.
- Yes. They're right over there.

326
00:36:24,152 --> 00:36:29,944
I haven't spoken to her family yet,
but I'm sure we can work it out.

327
00:36:30,111 --> 00:36:33,527
This is yours?
Where'd you get it?

328
00:36:33,695 --> 00:36:38,278
The history teacher. When he died,
he left me his gun collection.

329
00:36:38,444 --> 00:36:40,528
I'm taking this with me.

330
00:36:40,694 --> 00:36:43,695
- And I'm taking Alberte's things.
- Of course.

331
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:47,361
Move out of the way, please.

332
00:36:47,527 --> 00:36:50,777
You're very pretty, Rose.

333
00:36:51,777 --> 00:36:55,486
You need to move, now.

334
00:37:02,986 --> 00:37:07,611
Well done, sweetie.

335
00:37:23,861 --> 00:37:27,028
Where's that box?

336
00:37:28,569 --> 00:37:31,320
Have you got anything else
of Alberte's?

337
00:37:31,485 --> 00:37:34,278
- Is this everything?
- Yes, goddammit.

338
00:37:34,444 --> 00:37:38,944
38 stitches? They could hardly
stop the bleeding. 38 stitches.

339
00:37:39,111 --> 00:37:42,111
I heard you.

340
00:37:42,277 --> 00:37:45,777
- It was a bit much, Rose.
- It was self-defence. Understood?

341
00:37:45,945 --> 00:37:50,903
It was violence.
If Bak reports it, you'll be suspended.

342
00:37:51,070 --> 00:37:55,569
- So you're going to fire me? Again?
- Do you get that you went too far?

343
00:37:55,736 --> 00:37:58,152
I get it.

344
00:37:58,320 --> 00:38:03,110
- Do you need to talk?
- What I need is to work. Okay?

345
00:38:05,445 --> 00:38:08,070
Get a hold of yourself.

346
00:38:13,110 --> 00:38:16,570
- What's that?
- A kind of business card.

347
00:38:18,445 --> 00:38:24,110
I... I got an identical coin
at that lecture at the school.

348
00:38:24,278 --> 00:38:28,611
"The Osiris Academy of Enlightenment."

349
00:38:28,777 --> 00:38:32,778
She talked about the sun
and the light...

350
00:38:36,778 --> 00:38:40,485
Each muscle, each fibre,
each cell in your body -

351
00:38:40,653 --> 00:38:43,694
- loosens, relaxes, lets go.

352
00:38:45,820 --> 00:38:50,653
You're not your darkness.
You're not your pain.

353
00:38:50,819 --> 00:38:53,444
- You're not your fear.
- I'm not my fear.

354
00:39:11,027 --> 00:39:15,610
And let go. Let go.
And exhale.

355
00:39:19,485 --> 00:39:22,819
Can we talk in private?

356
00:39:31,319 --> 00:39:36,278
Wanda's gone missing,
and has been for a few days.

357
00:39:38,278 --> 00:39:41,277
Isn't she just in contemplative exile
somewhere?

358
00:39:41,445 --> 00:39:44,194
Have you checked the cleansing room?

359
00:39:44,361 --> 00:39:46,944
No. I haven't.

360
00:39:49,819 --> 00:39:53,360
We were meant to meet
on the North Cliff this morning.

361
00:39:53,528 --> 00:39:57,445
- She never came.
- Why didn't you tell me?

362
00:39:57,610 --> 00:40:01,110
We have a responsibility
for these people.

363
00:40:03,903 --> 00:40:05,986
Give her a little time.

364
00:40:51,027 --> 00:40:53,944
I wondered if you and Assad
would mind -

365
00:40:54,111 --> 00:40:57,569
- dealing with these Osiris people
tomorrow?

366
00:40:58,986 --> 00:41:01,360
Oh, how come?

367
00:41:03,236 --> 00:41:06,445
That woman's a bit too woo-woo for me.

368
00:41:08,445 --> 00:41:12,194
Sure. No problem.
It's a deal.

369
00:41:13,527 --> 00:41:16,486
What's up with you? Are you okay?

370
00:41:22,986 --> 00:41:26,402
- Bjarke...
- Yes?

371
00:41:29,236 --> 00:41:32,069
He was my son.

372
00:41:33,070 --> 00:41:35,985
- What?
- Yes.

373
00:41:41,986 --> 00:41:44,903
Holy shit.

374
00:41:47,319 --> 00:41:52,945
I don't know why I'm saying this.
I think I needed to tell someone.

375
00:41:53,986 --> 00:41:58,110
June just told me. She just...
I didn't know.

376
00:41:59,111 --> 00:42:02,820
It's a bit overwhelming,
to be honest.

377
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:12,944
Well...

378
00:42:13,111 --> 00:42:15,403
I'll just get this.

379
00:42:15,569 --> 00:42:17,860
- Hi, darling.
- Hi, Mona.

380
00:42:18,028 --> 00:42:21,986
- What are you up to?
- Oh, we're...

381
00:42:23,110 --> 00:42:25,861
- Not much.
- Did something happen?

382
00:42:26,027 --> 00:42:29,153
No, no. Everything's fine.
Just fine.

383
00:42:29,319 --> 00:42:33,611
- What's that sound?
- It's Assad. He's snoring.

384
00:42:33,777 --> 00:42:37,278
We're sharing a room.
I'm about to shoot him.

385
00:42:37,444 --> 00:42:41,069
- I miss you.
- I miss you too.

386
00:43:40,944 --> 00:43:46,945
- What are you doing here?
- I came to see the house one last time.

387
00:43:47,110 --> 00:43:49,570
This is Bjarke's childhood home.

388
00:43:52,153 --> 00:43:56,611
I'm sorry about the other day.
I got so angry. It wasn't fair.

389
00:43:56,777 --> 00:44:00,195
Don't worry about it.
And likewise.

390
00:44:10,235 --> 00:44:14,611
Did Christian know?
That Bjarke was mine?

391
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:16,861
No.

392
00:44:18,610 --> 00:44:21,736
Did you tell Bjarke?

393
00:44:23,569 --> 00:44:26,653
- Maybe I should have.
- Why?

394
00:44:28,360 --> 00:44:31,402
The two of them were never close.

395
00:44:34,860 --> 00:44:40,236
What did Bjarke mean by what he wrote
on the mirror? "I'm sorry, Dad."

396
00:44:40,402 --> 00:44:45,402
I think Bjarke felt ashamed.

397
00:44:45,570 --> 00:44:49,028
He was special.
He had a diagnosis.

398
00:44:49,194 --> 00:44:55,861
Christian just couldn't accept it.
So Bjarke began taking drugs -

399
00:44:56,027 --> 00:45:00,694
- and was always in and out of rehab.
It ended in disaster.

400
00:45:00,861 --> 00:45:04,569
Eventually Christian stopped
talking to him.

401
00:45:04,736 --> 00:45:09,028
I'm sorry to hear that, June.
Sorry it ended up that way.

402
00:45:09,195 --> 00:45:11,360
Truly.

403
00:45:14,153 --> 00:45:18,235
You knew him best.
Why would he shoot himself that way?

404
00:45:20,819 --> 00:45:23,611
I don't know.

405
00:45:25,153 --> 00:45:29,528
He came out to see me
a few months ago.

406
00:45:29,694 --> 00:45:33,028
All confused,
rambling on about how...

407
00:45:34,819 --> 00:45:37,653
He thought Bjarke had killed Alberte.

408
00:45:37,819 --> 00:45:41,778
- That Bjarke did it? Why?
- I don't know.

409
00:45:41,944 --> 00:45:46,485
We got into a fight about it,
and he broke down.

410
00:45:46,653 --> 00:45:51,735
I think he couldn't take it anymore.
He was seeing ghosts everywhere.

411
00:45:59,736 --> 00:46:01,945
Carl speaking.

412
00:46:03,278 --> 00:46:05,945
I'll be right there.

413
00:46:22,652 --> 00:46:25,695
I have to go.

414
00:46:46,945 --> 00:46:50,735
THE ALBERTE SCHNEIDER CASE
CLOSES DOWN

415
00:46:55,653 --> 00:46:57,736
Let's go.

416
00:46:59,903 --> 00:47:04,236
- That church sure is round.
- Because it's a round church.

417
00:47:05,820 --> 00:47:09,902
Thank you, Carl.
Bornholm is certainly beautiful.

418
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:12,444
- You've never been here before?
- Nope.

419
00:47:12,611 --> 00:47:15,320
- Not ever?
- No, never.

420
00:47:16,402 --> 00:47:20,360
- It is beautiful, all right.
- Ever been to Baghdad?

421
00:47:20,528 --> 00:47:25,569
- Never? Not ever?
- No, I haven't been to Baghdad.

422
00:47:25,736 --> 00:47:28,069
Why the hell would I go there?

423
00:47:56,069 --> 00:47:58,570
Good. Let me see it again.

424
00:48:02,445 --> 00:48:04,736
Thank you.

425
00:48:04,902 --> 00:48:09,278
- Copenhagen Police.
- Welcome. I'm Pirjo.

426
00:48:09,444 --> 00:48:13,528
We'd like to ask you about Alberte
Schneider. She was a part of this, right?

427
00:48:13,694 --> 00:48:17,194
- Yes, she was.
- Is there someplace we could talk?

428
00:48:17,361 --> 00:48:20,070
Of course.

429
00:48:20,235 --> 00:48:22,611
- What was her name?
- Pirjo.

430
00:48:22,777 --> 00:48:24,360
- Piro?
- Pirjo.

431
00:48:24,528 --> 00:48:27,861
I remember Alberte perfectly well.

432
00:48:28,027 --> 00:48:30,194
We loved her.

433
00:48:30,361 --> 00:48:34,110
It was horrible, what happened.
Atu and I were devastated.

434
00:48:34,278 --> 00:48:39,278
- Who's Atu?
- Atu is our spiritual leader.

435
00:48:39,444 --> 00:48:44,652
He and I founded this place together.
This is our life's work.

436
00:48:45,695 --> 00:48:48,527
What was Alberte's relation
to the place?

437
00:48:48,695 --> 00:48:54,027
Alberte attended the folk high school,
but... But then she came to us.

438
00:48:54,195 --> 00:48:57,445
- Are you associated with the school?
- No.

439
00:48:57,610 --> 00:49:01,819
We go all over to talk about
what we believe in.

440
00:49:01,986 --> 00:49:04,903
What about this Atu?
Can we talk to him?

441
00:49:05,069 --> 00:49:11,111
Of course you can "talk to this Atu",
but right now -

442
00:49:11,277 --> 00:49:13,902
- he's on the North Cliff
for his morning prayer.

443
00:49:14,070 --> 00:49:17,444
That's where he recharges his batteries.

444
00:49:17,611 --> 00:49:21,027
Well, what else do you do
besides charging batteries?

445
00:49:21,195 --> 00:49:24,652
We praise the light,
and Osiris is our god.

446
00:49:24,820 --> 00:49:27,403
But above all, we work with love.

447
00:49:29,320 --> 00:49:32,236
A whole lot of love.

448
00:49:32,402 --> 00:49:34,777
I'll show you our generator.

449
00:49:34,945 --> 00:49:39,235
It collects power from thousands
of solar panels we've set up.

450
00:49:39,403 --> 00:49:43,569
- You sell the sun?
- It's our contribution to humanity.

451
00:49:43,736 --> 00:49:47,903
We supply ourselves and sell the rest.

452
00:49:48,069 --> 00:49:51,944
- That way, everyone can be here for free.
- How admirable.

453
00:49:52,111 --> 00:49:56,902
It's important for me to state
that we don't exploit members for money.

454
00:49:57,070 --> 00:50:01,236
We take care of them
and fulfil their needs.

455
00:50:01,402 --> 00:50:05,486
And if I wanted to join your club?
Then what?

456
00:50:05,652 --> 00:50:09,527
Do you, Carl?
All you have to do is stay here -

457
00:50:09,695 --> 00:50:12,402
- and spend seven days
in the cleansing room.

458
00:50:12,570 --> 00:50:16,985
I think I'll pass.
This Atu, when will he be back?

459
00:50:17,153 --> 00:50:21,028
Unfortunately,
I don't think he'll be back today.

460
00:50:21,194 --> 00:50:24,986
But I'm sure he'd be happy
to speak to you another time.

461
00:50:25,152 --> 00:50:27,402
I'll show you our solar panels.

462
00:50:27,570 --> 00:50:30,486
I think she seemed all right. That Pia.

463
00:50:30,652 --> 00:50:33,610
Pirjo, Carl.

464
00:50:33,778 --> 00:50:36,860
Prio.

465
00:50:37,028 --> 00:50:40,028
It always makes me depressed.

466
00:50:41,361 --> 00:50:43,444
I've seen enough of it in Iraq.

467
00:50:43,611 --> 00:50:47,902
People wearing identical clothes
thinking they have all the answers.

468
00:50:48,070 --> 00:50:51,569
But they don't.
They never do.

469
00:50:52,777 --> 00:50:57,820
- Yes?
- Marie Frandsen has been hospitalised.

470
00:50:57,985 --> 00:51:02,860
Someone cut her tongue out,
and Bak doesn't want you to know.

471
00:51:03,028 --> 00:51:05,569
Someone cut her tongue out?

472
00:51:19,819 --> 00:51:23,528
Marie,
I'm so sorry about what happened.

473
00:51:23,694 --> 00:51:27,360
But, um...
Can I ask you some questions?

474
00:51:27,528 --> 00:51:29,944
Did you see who it was?

475
00:51:32,695 --> 00:51:36,860
Was it a woman?
It was a man who did it.

476
00:51:37,986 --> 00:51:40,903
Do you know him?

477
00:51:41,069 --> 00:51:43,360
You know him?

478
00:51:43,528 --> 00:51:47,777
Can you try to tell me his name?
I know it's difficult.

479
00:52:00,028 --> 00:52:02,235
S?

480
00:52:04,236 --> 00:52:06,985
Just relax. Relax.

481
00:52:07,153 --> 00:52:09,820
Here. Try writing it.

482
00:52:15,235 --> 00:52:17,945
S, V...

483
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:22,985
K...

484
00:52:23,153 --> 00:52:25,610
SVK?

485
00:52:26,569 --> 00:52:30,403
That's all? SVK? Is that all you know?

486
00:52:31,527 --> 00:52:33,735
Do you know anything else?

487
00:52:36,570 --> 00:52:38,902
Is Lola here?

488
00:52:39,985 --> 00:52:42,445
No.

489
00:52:43,527 --> 00:52:46,069
How come?

490
00:52:54,361 --> 00:52:56,736
It's time.

491
00:53:00,320 --> 00:53:03,278
It is?

492
00:53:34,528 --> 00:53:36,860
We had guests?

493
00:53:39,278 --> 00:53:42,528
The police.

494
00:53:42,694 --> 00:53:45,944
They asked about Alberte.

495
00:53:47,445 --> 00:53:51,445
What did you tell them?

496
00:53:52,860 --> 00:53:55,444
I told it like it is.

497
00:53:56,570 --> 00:53:59,486
That we loved her.

498
00:53:59,652 --> 00:54:02,235
Yes, we did.

499
00:54:02,403 --> 00:54:05,152
Very dearly.

500
00:54:10,903 --> 00:54:13,069
Welcome to the local news.

501
00:54:13,236 --> 00:54:17,486
Reporting from today's press conference
about the woman -

502
00:54:17,652 --> 00:54:20,278
- whose body washed ashore today.

503
00:54:20,444 --> 00:54:25,153
The body was identified as 26-year-old
former folk high school student -

504
00:54:25,319 --> 00:54:29,902
- Wanda Hoffmann from Hamburg.
Her family has been notified.

505
00:54:30,070 --> 00:54:34,945
It's still too early
to exclude a criminal act.

506
00:54:35,110 --> 00:54:40,153
But the North Cliff is a known
suicide location for young people.

507
00:54:40,319 --> 00:54:45,902
What's going on, Carl? You're running
a full investigation behind my back?

508
00:54:46,070 --> 00:54:50,361
That's correct. The woman was
presumably four months along.

509
00:54:50,527 --> 00:54:52,820
She was pregnant.

510
00:54:54,694 --> 00:54:59,319
Did she jump of her own volition too?
Like Alberte jumped up in that tree?

511
00:54:59,485 --> 00:55:02,152
Fucking lousy police work.
You have no talent, Bak.

512
00:55:02,320 --> 00:55:05,320
- Why did you close that case?
- Shut the fuck up.

513
00:55:05,485 --> 00:55:10,111
The ferry leaves in an hour.
And that blockhead is going with you.

514
00:55:10,277 --> 00:55:14,736
And your psycho bimbo out there.
You're done here.

515
00:55:14,902 --> 00:55:18,028
The thing about you is
that you're dumb.

516
00:55:18,194 --> 00:55:21,153
Good, old-fashioned dumb.
Hillbilly-style dumb.

517
00:55:21,319 --> 00:55:26,652
Christian used to laugh and say:
"Luckily he's too dumb to be corrupt."

518
00:55:26,820 --> 00:55:31,611
- Did he laugh when you fucked June?
- No, but she did when you tried.

519
00:55:32,819 --> 00:55:36,610
Hey, hey, hey. Relax.
Relax!

520
00:55:36,778 --> 00:55:40,778
- Hey! Leave me alone.
- You've got one hour, Carl!

521
00:55:40,944 --> 00:55:45,236
Then you're out of here.
That goes for you too. And you.

522
00:55:49,652 --> 00:55:53,569
This is unbelievable.
Haabersaat shoots himself.

523
00:55:53,736 --> 00:55:57,152
His son OD's.
His sister-in-law loses her tongue.

524
00:55:57,320 --> 00:56:00,570
- And what do we do? We go home.
- No, we're kicked off the island.

525
00:56:00,735 --> 00:56:05,360
I told you it wasn't our case. We have
everything, we'll investigate from home.

526
00:56:05,528 --> 00:56:08,986
What about the caretaker?
Who's following up on the guns?

527
00:56:09,152 --> 00:56:12,444
The guns were registered and legal.

528
00:56:12,611 --> 00:56:16,153
And he's not going anywhere.
You made sure of that, Rose.

529
00:56:16,319 --> 00:56:19,652
But Carl, it is annoying
to deal with your old shit.

530
00:56:28,819 --> 00:56:33,195
Rose, did you tell those cult people
that you're with the police?

531
00:56:33,360 --> 00:56:36,527
No. Why?

532
00:56:36,695 --> 00:56:41,320
- You could become one of them.
- You want her to infiltrate them?

533
00:56:41,485 --> 00:56:45,820
Dig around. Alberte was part of it.
What did they think of her?

534
00:56:45,985 --> 00:56:47,736
Insane, we don't know who they are.

535
00:56:47,902 --> 00:56:54,152
They do yoga and grow vegetables.
Are you afraid she'll choke on a carrot?

536
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:58,861
The problem is
all of Bornholm's police are trailing us.

537
00:57:00,445 --> 00:57:04,070
When we park on the ferry,
you could sneak away.

538
00:57:04,235 --> 00:57:08,194
- I have a better idea.
- What's that?

539
00:57:08,361 --> 00:57:11,694
Assad, give me your phone.

540
00:57:11,861 --> 00:57:15,319
- Why?
- Just give it to me.

541
00:57:15,486 --> 00:57:19,320
You'll hand in your own.
Call me from this one, once a day.

542
00:57:19,485 --> 00:57:23,360
- Keep a low profile and blend in.
- Okay.

543
00:57:23,528 --> 00:57:27,402
- This is way too risky.
- Can I please just do my job?

544
00:57:27,570 --> 00:57:32,569
- This is a bad idea.
- I'm done with your sensitive bullshit.

545
00:57:32,736 --> 00:57:37,570
- This is not a well-thought-out plan.
- I'm an officer. I can wipe my own ass.

546
00:58:19,402 --> 00:58:24,111
- I'm the cleaner.
- No, you're more than that.

547
00:58:24,277 --> 00:58:26,569
I know who you are.

548
00:58:28,569 --> 00:58:31,361
You're Shirley, Wanda's friend.

549
00:58:31,527 --> 00:58:33,694
Yes.

550
00:58:35,110 --> 00:58:38,319
Are you nervous, Shirley?

551
00:58:38,486 --> 00:58:41,736
Come a bit closer.

552
00:58:41,902 --> 00:58:44,777
And stop. Breathe.

553
00:58:48,903 --> 00:58:52,902
- How long have you been here?
- Four months.

554
00:58:55,194 --> 00:58:58,860
Have you figured out
what you need to let go of?

555
00:59:00,360 --> 00:59:02,861
Not yet.

556
00:59:05,652 --> 00:59:10,736
I have. You don't need to be ashamed
of being a fat girl.

557
00:59:10,902 --> 00:59:15,236
You just have to say it out loud.
Then the pain will go away.

558
00:59:17,903 --> 00:59:22,319
We love you, Shirley. We know that
there's so much to love about you.

559
00:59:23,695 --> 00:59:27,402
You need to say:
"I'm a fat girl."

560
00:59:28,528 --> 00:59:31,778
I know it's hard,
but it will set you free.

561
00:59:35,902 --> 00:59:38,860
- I'm a fat girl.
- Louder.

562
00:59:41,194 --> 00:59:44,570
I'm a fat girl.

563
00:59:44,735 --> 00:59:47,070
Say it like you mean it.

564
00:59:47,235 --> 00:59:51,403
- I am a fat girl.
- I'm a fat girl.

565
00:59:51,569 --> 00:59:54,236
- I am a fat girl.
- You are a fat girl.

566
00:59:54,402 --> 00:59:58,735
- I'm a fat girl. I'm a fat girl.
- Enjoy saying it. Enjoy who you are.

567
00:59:58,903 --> 01:00:02,486
- I am a fat girl.
- Enjoy it!

568
01:00:07,235 --> 01:00:09,570
Well done.

569
01:00:12,027 --> 01:00:16,195
Take Wanda's belt with you.
She forgot it last time.

570
01:00:29,277 --> 01:00:34,860
I gave it to her, but it seemed like
it had been hidden beneath the mattress.

571
01:00:35,028 --> 01:00:39,360
You know that they were lovers.
Maybe it's just a coincidence.

572
01:00:39,528 --> 01:00:45,819
- No. She's been gone for four days.
- Then we'll go speak to Atu tomorrow.

573
01:00:45,986 --> 01:00:50,695
- Will you go to the police with me?
- Oh, Shirley.

574
01:00:50,860 --> 01:00:55,570
- Is that really necessary?
- Yes. Something feels very wrong.

575
01:00:58,902 --> 01:01:02,902
Okay. If you feel so strongly about it,
we'll do it.

576
01:01:03,860 --> 01:01:06,985
Thank you.

577
01:01:07,153 --> 01:01:09,735
Oh, poor thing.

578
01:02:01,152 --> 01:02:04,570
- Carl!
- Help Assad.

579
01:02:04,735 --> 01:02:08,569
- Hello.
- Hi, Gordon.

580
01:02:22,153 --> 01:02:27,194
- Gordon, didn't you study art history?
- Sure, for a few semesters.

581
01:02:27,361 --> 01:02:31,486
Take a look at these drawings.
Alberte did them.

582
01:02:34,070 --> 01:02:37,320
She had talent.
Her line is impressive.

583
01:02:37,485 --> 01:02:40,069
It's the same man in all the drawings.

584
01:02:40,236 --> 01:02:46,445
The dimensions are the same.
Same broad shoulders. Narrow waist.

585
01:02:46,610 --> 01:02:51,194
That one down there. It's the only
woman. I think it's a self-portrait.

586
01:02:51,361 --> 01:02:53,569
Is she pregnant?

587
01:02:53,736 --> 01:02:57,110
- Maybe.
- That curve of her belly.

588
01:02:57,278 --> 01:03:01,610
That red pigment beneath
his left armpit repeats too.

589
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:06,152
- That must've been important to her.
- What do you think it is?

590
01:03:06,320 --> 01:03:09,444
Dunno. A wound? A tattoo, maybe?

591
01:03:09,611 --> 01:03:12,820
- What do you think, Assad?
- Very nice.

592
01:03:12,985 --> 01:03:16,985
Very nice?
Thanks for your input.

593
01:03:19,194 --> 01:03:22,194
He's looking over his shoulder here.

594
01:03:56,944 --> 01:03:59,153
Bloody hell.

595
01:03:59,319 --> 01:04:02,403
- They're siblings.
- Who?

596
01:04:02,569 --> 01:04:06,110
- Pirjo. And that guy Atu.
- What makes you think that?

597
01:04:06,278 --> 01:04:13,153
- This note, among Habersaat's papers.
- Life is short and replete with fear.

598
01:04:13,319 --> 01:04:16,361
Fear of the violence...

599
01:04:16,527 --> 01:04:21,611
The drought,
the power psychoses of old men...

600
01:04:21,777 --> 01:04:24,319
Clowns.

601
01:04:24,486 --> 01:04:27,527
They have the same mother,
from near Stockholm -

602
01:04:27,695 --> 01:04:32,986
- but two different fathers.
One is Danish, the other Swedish.

603
01:04:37,570 --> 01:04:40,695
Pirjo was sent to an orphanage
at the age of four -

604
01:04:40,860 --> 01:04:44,028
- while Atu went to his father
in Copenhagen.

605
01:04:44,194 --> 01:04:50,069
His father was an addict too, so Atu
was later removed by the authorities.

606
01:04:50,236 --> 01:04:55,320
- But are we afraid? Are we afraid?
- No. No!

607
01:04:55,485 --> 01:04:58,570
Pirjo and Atu have no contact
in those years...

608
01:04:58,735 --> 01:05:02,652
No, we aren't afraid.
Because we've stepped into the light.

609
01:05:02,820 --> 01:05:05,902
But they reconnect as teenagers.

610
01:05:06,070 --> 01:05:11,611
They bonded strongly, Habersaat writes.
An "us versus the world" logic.

611
01:05:11,777 --> 01:05:16,985
We know. Us right here, we know.
But right out there, they don't know.

612
01:05:17,153 --> 01:05:21,860
They don't understand that to heal
the world, we have to heal ourselves.

613
01:05:22,028 --> 01:05:26,028
They founded the cult in 2008,
and it quickly gained a following.

614
01:05:26,194 --> 01:05:28,570
And our numbers are growing.

615
01:05:28,735 --> 01:05:33,736
- Just look at this new, beautiful face.
- That's Rose.

616
01:05:35,070 --> 01:05:40,735
You've come to a place where
we thank the sun for life and its gifts.

617
01:05:40,903 --> 01:05:44,027
We're not a religion.
Religions eclipse the sun.

618
01:05:44,195 --> 01:05:47,195
They're humans' attempt
to systematise fear.

619
01:05:47,360 --> 01:05:53,653
We prefer to let go of the fear that's
preventing you, Rose, from being you.

620
01:06:00,360 --> 01:06:03,736
Let's welcome her.

621
01:06:13,360 --> 01:06:18,111
- This is too suspicious, Carl.
- Just because they have other beliefs?

622
01:06:18,277 --> 01:06:23,360
No, because Rose is there, among them.
That's what worries me.

623
01:06:40,944 --> 01:06:43,277
Hi!

624
01:06:45,277 --> 01:06:49,485
I took the liberty to hang some clothes
for you.

625
01:06:49,653 --> 01:06:52,735
- Oh, that's for me? Thanks.
- If you'd like.

626
01:06:52,903 --> 01:06:55,944
Everything here is voluntary.

627
01:06:57,235 --> 01:07:00,111
I'm so glad you came.

628
01:07:02,444 --> 01:07:08,027
But, if you'd like,
I'd love to accept your phone.

629
01:07:08,195 --> 01:07:10,319
Yes, of course.

630
01:07:12,527 --> 01:07:15,070
Here you go.

631
01:07:23,652 --> 01:07:28,527
Come into the light, lovely Rose.

632
01:07:38,403 --> 01:07:42,111
Okay, so we've got Bjarke.
We've got Simon Fabian.

633
01:07:42,277 --> 01:07:46,236
And we've got Stefan von Kristoff.

634
01:07:46,402 --> 01:07:50,570
- We have... Mickey...
- What did you say his name was?

635
01:07:51,944 --> 01:07:57,152
Stefan von Kristoff.
Alberte's art teacher at the school.

636
01:07:57,320 --> 01:08:01,653
- SVK?
- Yes... So what?

637
01:08:01,819 --> 01:08:06,861
Crazy-Marie, whose tongue was cut out,
wrote SVK when I asked her who did it.

638
01:08:07,027 --> 01:08:12,570
- I couldn't figure out who it was.
- What's his deal?

639
01:08:12,735 --> 01:08:18,319
Christian Habersaat believed
that they had a relationship...

640
01:08:20,652 --> 01:08:25,110
In the image in Habersaat's house
she has a tattoo on her calf.

641
01:08:25,278 --> 01:08:30,528
Or, I thought it was a tattoo.
It isn't there in any other photos.

642
01:08:33,069 --> 01:08:37,277
I think it's a signature.
SVK's signature.

643
01:08:37,445 --> 01:08:40,695
The picture of Alberte is an artwork.

644
01:08:41,735 --> 01:08:45,610
- He can't just be some sleazy teacher.
- Former teacher.

645
01:08:45,778 --> 01:08:50,445
He gets fired
due to inappropriate sexual behaviour.

646
01:08:50,610 --> 01:08:54,069
We're onto something here.
Find out where he lives.

647
01:09:26,861 --> 01:09:29,403
Copenhagen Police.

648
01:09:31,111 --> 01:09:35,110
Hey! Copenhagen Police.

649
01:09:35,278 --> 01:09:37,485
Turn that thing off.

650
01:09:37,653 --> 01:09:40,153
Turn it off.

651
01:09:43,235 --> 01:09:46,485
- Are you SVK... What was it?
- Stefan von Kristoff.

652
01:09:46,653 --> 01:09:52,110
We're here regarding Alberte Schneider,
your former student. Is that correct?

653
01:09:52,278 --> 01:09:55,360
Yes, that's me.
And I know why you're here.

654
01:09:55,528 --> 01:09:59,610
You've finally realised that I took
that photo of Alberte in the tree -

655
01:09:59,778 --> 01:10:03,110
- and you're thinking:
"My, my. He must be the murderer."

656
01:10:03,278 --> 01:10:06,945
But I'll have to disappoint you,
because it isn't me.

657
01:10:07,110 --> 01:10:10,153
So let's not waste each other's time.

658
01:10:10,319 --> 01:10:14,235
- Tell us about that picture.
- Not much to tell.

659
01:10:14,403 --> 01:10:19,653
I found Alberte in the tree early
one morning and I took the picture.

660
01:10:19,819 --> 01:10:25,569
That picture was my breakthrough.
I've sold thousands of copies.

661
01:10:25,736 --> 01:10:28,736
- Where do you sell it?
- Online.

662
01:10:28,902 --> 01:10:33,069
- The dark web?
- Yes. I'm big in the dark.

663
01:10:34,570 --> 01:10:39,736
- How did you take the picture?
- With my camera.

664
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:43,695
What were you doing out there
so early in the morning?

665
01:10:43,860 --> 01:10:48,195
There's something you have to
know about Alberte.

666
01:10:48,360 --> 01:10:54,652
Alberte was by far the most
talented student I ever had.

667
01:10:54,820 --> 01:11:00,320
I was envious of her.
Yes, I envied her a little.

668
01:11:01,777 --> 01:11:05,195
At one point, she wanted
to learn to draw animals.

669
01:11:05,360 --> 01:11:11,986
So we cycled out early in the morning
and found them. Untouched roadkill.

670
01:11:12,152 --> 01:11:14,402
Then we cycled back.

671
01:11:14,570 --> 01:11:18,570
I didn't teach her to draw.
She knew how to do that.

672
01:11:18,735 --> 01:11:21,695
I taught her to see.

673
01:11:21,860 --> 01:11:24,653
I taught her to see beyond the surface.

674
01:11:24,819 --> 01:11:27,361
Did you have a relationship?

675
01:11:29,195 --> 01:11:34,070
- I was in love with Alberte.
- Was it reciprocal?

676
01:11:35,569 --> 01:11:39,028
I thought so.
For a brief while.

677
01:11:41,570 --> 01:11:44,110
Until she got pregnant with someone else.

678
01:11:44,278 --> 01:11:47,319
Pregnant with who?

679
01:11:47,486 --> 01:11:49,736
It wasn't you?

680
01:11:51,361 --> 01:11:54,236
Knocking up a student
isn't a great career move.

681
01:11:54,402 --> 01:11:58,236
I had no career.
That's what was so humiliating.

682
01:11:58,402 --> 01:12:03,194
- How?
- As a man without success. As an artist.

683
01:12:03,361 --> 01:12:06,902
- You know how that stuff works.
- How does it work?

684
01:12:09,903 --> 01:12:16,778
One makes an effort, one toils away,
one hopes, one falls in love.

685
01:12:16,944 --> 01:12:22,110
And then one is left.
One is made a fool of.

686
01:12:22,278 --> 01:12:26,319
And then one finds out
the whole world doesn't give a shit.

687
01:12:28,277 --> 01:12:30,695
So that morning, you found Alberte.

688
01:12:30,860 --> 01:12:34,860
Yes, I found Alberte by the tree.
Dead...

689
01:12:35,028 --> 01:12:38,735
Hit by a car.
And then I took that picture.

690
01:12:38,903 --> 01:12:43,277
By the tree?
You said, "by the tree".

691
01:12:43,445 --> 01:12:49,570
- The police found Alberte in the tree.
- In the tree. I found her in the tree.

692
01:12:49,735 --> 01:12:55,570
- Did you find her in or by the tree?
- In it. I photographed her in the tree.

693
01:12:55,735 --> 01:12:59,361
- That's what I'm saying.
- So why didn't you call the police?

694
01:12:59,527 --> 01:13:03,194
Instead you start taking pictures.
You know what I think?

695
01:13:03,361 --> 01:13:07,195
I think you killed Alberte,
hoisted her into the tree -

696
01:13:07,360 --> 01:13:11,736
- snapped your photos and got famous
among a bunch of necrophile idiots.

697
01:13:17,402 --> 01:13:19,570
Stefan?

698
01:13:22,528 --> 01:13:27,695
The woman called Marie Frandsen,
from Bornholm. You know her?

699
01:13:29,860 --> 01:13:33,653
- No.
- They call her Crazy-Marie.

700
01:13:33,819 --> 01:13:37,360
She says she knows you.

701
01:13:51,861 --> 01:13:54,277
For fuck's sake!

702
01:13:54,445 --> 01:13:57,070
- Good morning, Rose.
- Good morning.

703
01:13:58,278 --> 01:14:00,361
Atu wants to see you.

704
01:14:08,403 --> 01:14:11,736
What exactly is happening?

705
01:14:26,320 --> 01:14:28,986
- Only one.
- Oh, right. Only one.

706
01:14:32,820 --> 01:14:35,652
Pirjo speaks so highly of you, Rose.

707
01:14:35,820 --> 01:14:38,819
Oh, does she?

708
01:14:40,235 --> 01:14:42,653
Thanks.

709
01:14:45,153 --> 01:14:47,902
It made me so eager to meet you.

710
01:14:51,111 --> 01:14:54,903
- Do you like it here?
- Yes.

711
01:14:56,069 --> 01:14:59,610
- It's exciting.
- Do you mind if I just look at you?

712
01:14:59,778 --> 01:15:02,027
Is that weird?

713
01:15:03,028 --> 01:15:06,361
No, no.
Or... It's fine.

714
01:15:09,402 --> 01:15:11,861
Give me your hands.

715
01:15:15,277 --> 01:15:19,320
I'm going to ask you some questions,
but don't answer them.

716
01:15:19,485 --> 01:15:21,028
Okay.

717
01:15:25,903 --> 01:15:28,652
Are you on guard, Rose?

718
01:15:33,028 --> 01:15:36,028
Do you believe me?

719
01:15:39,861 --> 01:15:42,445
Who is your best friend?

720
01:15:42,610 --> 01:15:45,111
Did he take happiness with him?

721
01:15:45,277 --> 01:15:48,152
And leave you with shame?

722
01:15:50,278 --> 01:15:52,861
Do you miss the orgasm?

723
01:15:57,195 --> 01:16:00,485
Can you forgive the evil?

724
01:16:00,653 --> 01:16:03,570
Is the pain greater than the meaning?

725
01:16:06,820 --> 01:16:10,069
Next question I want you to answer:

726
01:16:13,527 --> 01:16:17,819
Are you sad, Rose?
Tell me about it.

727
01:16:25,944 --> 01:16:29,736
- I can't.
- Was it a man?

728
01:16:29,902 --> 01:16:33,485
A man who was meant
to take care of you?

729
01:16:33,653 --> 01:16:37,111
But he didn't take care of you.
He hurt you.

730
01:16:39,695 --> 01:16:42,569
Did he abuse you?

731
01:16:46,986 --> 01:16:49,903
Was it your father?

732
01:16:55,235 --> 01:17:00,069
He went on.
And on, and on, and on...

733
01:17:09,610 --> 01:17:12,235
I couldn't take anymore.

734
01:17:14,653 --> 01:17:17,069
So one day I beat him up.

735
01:17:17,236 --> 01:17:20,319
Thrashed and battered him.

736
01:17:21,486 --> 01:17:24,860
Destroyed him.

737
01:17:25,028 --> 01:17:28,069
He was hospitalised.

738
01:17:29,069 --> 01:17:33,736
When they discharged him
from the hospital...

739
01:17:33,902 --> 01:17:36,944
He hanged himself.

740
01:17:43,236 --> 01:17:45,486
It was me.

741
01:17:46,528 --> 01:17:49,736
- I killed him.
- No, you didn't.

742
01:17:49,902 --> 01:17:54,777
You fought for your life.
He made holes in your soul.

743
01:17:54,945 --> 01:17:58,985
That's the worst thing you can do
to a person.

744
01:17:59,153 --> 01:18:02,027
Now we'll fill them with light.

745
01:18:02,195 --> 01:18:07,945
Look into my eyes. There's no fear.
There's only light.

746
01:18:08,110 --> 01:18:11,402
There's no fear.
There's only light.

747
01:18:11,570 --> 01:18:16,528
There's no fear. There's only light.
No fear, only light.

748
01:18:18,028 --> 01:18:20,278
I'm with you.

749
01:18:21,278 --> 01:18:23,903
I am in you.

750
01:18:26,110 --> 01:18:31,070
The sun is in my hands.
Feel them get warmer.

751
01:18:31,235 --> 01:18:34,361
Warmer, and warmer, and warmer.

752
01:18:34,527 --> 01:18:38,777
There's no fear. There's only light.
No fear, only light.

753
01:18:40,236 --> 01:18:42,402
You're safe.

754
01:18:45,277 --> 01:18:47,695
Sleep.

755
01:18:52,278 --> 01:18:54,861
- Did you buy it?
- Yes, I got it.

756
01:18:55,027 --> 01:18:59,778
- Have you heard from the lab?
- I'm still waiting on the DNA samples.

757
01:18:59,944 --> 01:19:04,735
I'm going to call Rose.
There's been no word for three days.

758
01:19:04,903 --> 01:19:08,778
- Carl, they've called from...
- Just a moment.

759
01:19:08,944 --> 01:19:12,235
It's important. The duty officer says
SVK wants to talk.

760
01:19:12,403 --> 01:19:16,819
- The case isn't complete yet.
- But he wants to confess to something.

761
01:19:16,986 --> 01:19:21,735
- What?
- That he pulled Alberte into the tree.

762
01:19:26,486 --> 01:19:31,361
Then I found her at the roadside,
bleeding from her nose...

763
01:19:31,527 --> 01:19:34,027
And from her head, her ears.

764
01:19:34,195 --> 01:19:36,570
She was so beautiful.

765
01:19:38,652 --> 01:19:41,153
White as a ghost.

766
01:19:41,319 --> 01:19:44,235
Ice cold. She had no pulse.

767
01:19:47,069 --> 01:19:50,027
So I took a picture.
And another.

768
01:19:52,403 --> 01:19:58,070
Then I had the idea of lifting her up
into the tree and arranging her there.

769
01:19:59,735 --> 01:20:04,360
When I did it, I knew: This was
the most beautiful sight I'd ever see.

770
01:20:04,528 --> 01:20:06,778
And that's my crime.

771
01:20:06,944 --> 01:20:09,944
I didn't kill her.

772
01:20:10,111 --> 01:20:12,777
I found her,
and I did something unforgivable.

773
01:20:12,945 --> 01:20:16,570
That's why I didn't contact
the police that morning.

774
01:20:16,735 --> 01:20:19,610
I regret it every day.

775
01:20:20,778 --> 01:20:23,653
I'd like to believe you, Stefan.

776
01:20:23,819 --> 01:20:28,110
For a man so full of regret,
your crime paid off quite well.

777
01:20:28,278 --> 01:20:33,861
- How much did you charge for the photo?
- I haven't sold it yet.

778
01:20:34,027 --> 01:20:37,320
- You said you've sold thousands.
- Not the original.

779
01:20:37,485 --> 01:20:41,527
- Why not?
- Because the piece isn't finished.

780
01:20:41,695 --> 01:20:45,360
- When will it be finished?
- Once I'm finished.

781
01:20:48,861 --> 01:20:51,445
Hi, Klaus.
Just put it there.

782
01:20:53,485 --> 01:20:55,653
Thanks.

783
01:20:59,486 --> 01:21:03,820
You were in Bornholm last Wednesday.
Did you visit Marie Frandsen?

784
01:21:03,985 --> 01:21:06,361
I told you, I don't know who she is.

785
01:21:06,527 --> 01:21:10,236
Marie Frandsen had her tongue cut out
last Wednesday.

786
01:21:16,319 --> 01:21:19,860
Assad bought this on your online portal
for 66,000 kroner.

787
01:21:20,028 --> 01:21:23,777
We've taken some DNA samples.
It's Marie Frandsen's tongue.

788
01:21:23,945 --> 01:21:28,902
Oh? I don't know where
my material comes from.

789
01:21:29,070 --> 01:21:32,569
It could be anyone's tongue.

790
01:21:32,736 --> 01:21:37,861
That's the work. That's the context
in which it should be understood.

791
01:21:38,027 --> 01:21:41,069
Are you sad you never got
your own exhibition?

792
01:21:41,236 --> 01:21:43,902
- What?
- I've made some calls.

793
01:21:44,070 --> 01:21:48,152
You once held such promise
at the Academy of Art. What happened?

794
01:21:48,320 --> 01:21:51,528
How did you end up
at some lousy folk high school?

795
01:21:51,694 --> 01:21:54,278
It must have been a huge defeat.

796
01:21:55,610 --> 01:22:00,111
- My art isn't for everyone.
- You can say that again.

797
01:22:00,277 --> 01:22:05,195
And there's Alberte.
So full of talent.

798
01:22:05,360 --> 01:22:08,110
And so she had to die.

799
01:22:09,486 --> 01:22:13,527
I've done my homework, Stefan.
You're a nobody.

800
01:22:13,695 --> 01:22:18,278
You've always been a nobody,
and you always will be.

801
01:22:18,444 --> 01:22:24,694
Your audience is necrophiliacs
who get off on corpses and cut-off limbs.

802
01:22:26,695 --> 01:22:32,570
There's another thing. You said Alberte
was bleeding from her nose and ears.

803
01:22:32,735 --> 01:22:36,069
It's just that dead people don't bleed.

804
01:22:38,235 --> 01:22:40,319
No.

805
01:22:41,319 --> 01:22:44,986
She was alive when you found her?

806
01:22:49,903 --> 01:22:55,028
Are you finished?
You sure are clever, aren't you?

807
01:22:55,194 --> 01:22:59,485
You've really been practising.
May I borrow your computer?

808
01:22:59,653 --> 01:23:02,236
- For what?
- Go ahead.

809
01:23:02,402 --> 01:23:08,277
Now, take a look
and tell me what you see.

810
01:23:09,320 --> 01:23:13,278
Now tell me, why is SVK big in the dark?

811
01:23:16,278 --> 01:23:19,694
Now she's alive. Now she's dead.

812
01:23:19,861 --> 01:23:23,194
Now she's alive. Now she's dead.

813
01:23:23,361 --> 01:23:26,194
Now she's alive, now she's dead.

814
01:23:26,361 --> 01:23:30,110
A young girl's final breath,
right there.

815
01:23:30,278 --> 01:23:33,027
Right at that moment.

816
01:23:44,985 --> 01:23:48,736
No one's ever done that before.

817
01:23:48,902 --> 01:23:55,278
- She was alive when you put her there.
- She was dying. I didn't kill her.

818
01:23:57,278 --> 01:24:01,778
- You're a sick person.
- I'm SVK.

819
01:24:06,569 --> 01:24:09,236
- Do you think he did it?
- Don't you agree?

820
01:24:09,402 --> 01:24:12,945
- But why won't he confess?
- He's hoping to get off lightly.

821
01:24:13,110 --> 01:24:17,820
- Maybe he hit her by accident.
- It's simple. He was in love with her.

822
01:24:17,985 --> 01:24:22,402
So he killed her and turned her
into an art installation.

823
01:24:22,570 --> 01:24:24,903
I'll just call Rose.

824
01:24:46,860 --> 01:24:49,235
How are you feeling?

825
01:24:51,777 --> 01:24:56,319
- I'm well.
- Good.

826
01:24:58,027 --> 01:25:00,986
Yes.

827
01:25:01,152 --> 01:25:04,777
Now.
Eat, my darling.

828
01:25:06,069 --> 01:25:08,486
Thank you.

829
01:25:15,403 --> 01:25:17,695
Look into my eyes.

830
01:25:17,860 --> 01:25:21,570
Light is strength.
Light is power.

831
01:25:23,570 --> 01:25:28,152
Light is strength. Light is power.

832
01:25:28,320 --> 01:25:30,986
I am the light.

833
01:25:34,195 --> 01:25:37,861
Light is strength. Light is power.

834
01:25:38,027 --> 01:25:41,277
Light is strength. Light is power.

835
01:25:41,445 --> 01:25:45,819
I am light.
The light is in me.

836
01:25:46,819 --> 01:25:51,319
I am light.
The light is in me.

837
01:25:51,486 --> 01:25:55,403
I am light. The light is me.

838
01:25:56,860 --> 01:26:02,694
Use me to drive out the darkness.
I am nothing. Light is everything.

839
01:26:02,861 --> 01:26:06,360
I am nothing. The light is everything.

840
01:26:06,528 --> 01:26:09,986
Light is strength. Light is power.

841
01:26:10,152 --> 01:26:14,110
Light is strength. Light is power.

842
01:27:14,236 --> 01:27:17,111
You're happy.

843
01:27:20,569 --> 01:27:22,735
Are you...?

844
01:27:27,277 --> 01:27:29,985
Finally.

845
01:27:30,153 --> 01:27:33,361
A child of the sun.
Pure in bloodline.

846
01:27:33,527 --> 01:27:36,110
Little sister.

847
01:27:36,278 --> 01:27:39,027
Mother would have been proud.

848
01:27:40,360 --> 01:27:43,736
- Do you think so?
- Yes.

849
01:27:58,527 --> 01:28:00,986
Finally.

850
01:28:05,236 --> 01:28:08,611
We celebrate the conception
of a child of the sun.

851
01:28:08,777 --> 01:28:14,152
A child of a goddess. A child who carries
the light inside. Who is the light.

852
01:28:14,320 --> 01:28:18,485
We celebrate the conception
of a child of the sun.

853
01:28:18,653 --> 01:28:24,069
A child who carries the light inside.
He shall arrive in flesh and blood.

854
01:28:24,236 --> 01:28:27,277
Shall pass on the light to all
who accept it -

855
01:28:27,445 --> 01:28:31,611
- and so all will be possible.
All is possible.

856
01:28:31,777 --> 01:28:34,110
All is possible!

857
01:28:45,819 --> 01:28:49,195
She's turned off her phone.

858
01:28:52,070 --> 01:28:55,111
- Yes?
- Are you sitting down?

859
01:28:55,277 --> 01:29:00,110
- We're in the car. What do you think?
- SVK has escaped.

860
01:29:00,278 --> 01:29:04,778
Escaped? Surely he's being monitored?

861
01:29:04,944 --> 01:29:10,403
I was told
that he banged his head into the wall.

862
01:29:10,569 --> 01:29:13,402
Again and again
until blood sprayed out.

863
01:29:13,570 --> 01:29:17,319
He called a guard
and was sent to the emergency room.

864
01:29:17,486 --> 01:29:20,528
I've sent you a video. Take a look.

865
01:29:23,569 --> 01:29:29,861
The officers guarding the entrance
didn't check for other exits.

866
01:29:30,027 --> 01:29:34,403
So, SVK just gets up
and walks out the back door.

867
01:29:34,569 --> 01:29:37,235
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

868
01:29:37,403 --> 01:29:42,735
- Bloody amateurs.
- Everybody is out looking for him.

869
01:29:42,903 --> 01:29:46,486
- How do I rewind?
- The button on the left.

870
01:29:52,902 --> 01:29:58,069
- What is he saying?
- Something he needs to do.

871
01:29:59,153 --> 01:30:05,277
I have something I need to complete.
I hate unfinished work.

872
01:30:11,152 --> 01:30:15,069
Gordon, are you there?
I think I know where he is.

873
01:30:15,235 --> 01:30:20,152
We're on our way to his workplace.
We need backup, fast.

874
01:30:51,611 --> 01:30:53,985
Welcome!

875
01:30:55,236 --> 01:30:59,569
Tonight, my artwork featuring Alberte
will be completed.

876
01:30:59,736 --> 01:31:01,986
And to think, you are a part of it!

877
01:31:02,152 --> 01:31:05,777
So come closer,
walk towards the light.

878
01:31:09,610 --> 01:31:12,902
We have our masterpieces.

879
01:31:16,152 --> 01:31:21,903
We have men with guns,
we have the whirr of cameras -

880
01:31:22,069 --> 01:31:25,195
- so smile at the darkness.

881
01:31:25,360 --> 01:31:30,653
Because they're watching you.
The whole world is your audience.

882
01:31:32,278 --> 01:31:35,110
Stop.

883
01:31:35,278 --> 01:31:39,153
Yes, where am I?

884
01:31:40,736 --> 01:31:44,736
Look at the shadow.
Is that me?

885
01:31:47,694 --> 01:31:51,027
- Hands up so we can see them.
- Stop when I tell you to.

886
01:31:55,695 --> 01:31:59,278
- Hey.
- Hey, Stefan!

887
01:32:05,985 --> 01:32:10,320
- Was it real? Is it me hanging there?
- Where the hell is he?

888
01:32:10,485 --> 01:32:14,735
No. The shadow isn't real.
Look at it. I've invented him.

889
01:32:14,903 --> 01:32:20,027
The shadow doesn't give a shit.
He does whatever he wants.

890
01:32:20,195 --> 01:32:23,527
He invades other artworks.

891
01:32:24,986 --> 01:32:31,110
Tonight he invades my work,
which consists of Alberte in the tree.

892
01:32:31,278 --> 01:32:37,028
A poor artist who was
at the right place at the wrong time.

893
01:32:37,194 --> 01:32:40,819
And you, primates with guns.

894
01:32:42,653 --> 01:32:47,569
Is that the real story of Alberte?
Is it true?

895
01:32:47,736 --> 01:32:50,902
But what is real? What is true?

896
01:32:51,070 --> 01:32:56,236
Isn't it all just tricks
waiting to be revealed?

897
01:32:57,236 --> 01:33:02,235
Like the life you think you live,
versus the one you're actually living.

898
01:33:02,403 --> 01:33:06,320
Like Alberte who was killed
by a roadside -

899
01:33:06,485 --> 01:33:08,777
- but died in a tree.

900
01:33:10,152 --> 01:33:16,360
How pathetic I was at that school.
What pathetic lives we lead.

901
01:33:16,528 --> 01:33:20,986
But it wasn't me.
It wasn't me who did it!

902
01:33:21,152 --> 01:33:25,945
But you refuse to believe that!
Look towards the light!

903
01:33:26,110 --> 01:33:31,985
How pathetic I was at that school.
What pathetic lives we lead.

904
01:33:32,153 --> 01:33:37,278
- Hands up so we can see them!
- Look towards the light.

905
01:33:37,444 --> 01:33:40,528
- The sun will guide you.
- Put them up.

906
01:33:55,319 --> 01:33:57,403
Farewell.

907
01:33:57,569 --> 01:34:00,778
It was less fun than expected.

908
01:34:00,944 --> 01:34:04,320
But at least
the artwork has been completed.

909
01:34:05,945 --> 01:34:09,069
Do you take that as a confession?

910
01:34:53,610 --> 01:34:56,944
- It's Carl.
- Hi, it's June.

911
01:34:57,111 --> 01:35:00,527
- Did I wake you?
- Yes.

912
01:35:00,695 --> 01:35:05,319
Oh, sorry. I've been up all night
looking at old photos -

913
01:35:05,486 --> 01:35:09,527
- of Bjarke as a baby.
And I was just wondering -

914
01:35:09,695 --> 01:35:13,527
- if you might want
to see some of them?

915
01:35:13,695 --> 01:35:15,528
Sure, I do.

916
01:35:15,694 --> 01:35:19,610
Would you like to come over tonight
for a glass of wine?

917
01:35:19,778 --> 01:35:23,819
I would, but I've left Bornholm.

918
01:35:23,986 --> 01:35:27,735
Oh, well, it was just a thought.
Call me if you come back.

919
01:35:27,903 --> 01:35:31,360
- I will.
- Carl?

920
01:35:32,402 --> 01:35:36,736
- I hope you know that I did my best.
- What?

921
01:35:36,902 --> 01:35:41,570
- Right, of course.
- I'll send you the pictures.

922
01:35:45,528 --> 01:35:48,486
Who was it?

923
01:35:48,652 --> 01:35:52,778
A woman in deep grief.
She just lost her son.

924
01:35:54,735 --> 01:35:56,986
How tragic.

925
01:35:57,152 --> 01:35:59,570
Terribly tragic.

926
01:36:08,527 --> 01:36:10,694
Mona?

927
01:36:15,236 --> 01:36:17,860
He was my son, too.

928
01:36:20,028 --> 01:36:24,735
I knew her thirty years ago.
She just never told me...

929
01:36:24,903 --> 01:36:27,652
- That it was your son?
- Yes.

930
01:36:28,820 --> 01:36:31,985
It stirs up a lot of old stuff.

931
01:36:34,986 --> 01:36:37,527
Okay.

932
01:36:43,027 --> 01:36:47,361
Carl.
You've got to sort it out.

933
01:36:49,569 --> 01:36:54,694
Do what needs to be done,
and come home when you feel ready.

934
01:36:58,695 --> 01:37:02,444
Because I hope you will.

935
01:37:50,778 --> 01:37:54,235
- Superintendent Birkedal.
- It's Carl Mørck.

936
01:37:54,403 --> 01:38:00,402
I was wondering, what did the autopsy
say about Bjarke Habersaat?

937
01:38:00,570 --> 01:38:04,903
It said: "Cause of death, overdose."

938
01:38:05,069 --> 01:38:10,070
- "Full of heroin, vodka and benzos."
- Did you find anything at his house?

939
01:38:10,235 --> 01:38:14,570
Yeah, some old payslips and a computer
with some photos. I haven't looked at it.

940
01:38:14,735 --> 01:38:19,069
- Could you send it to me?
- Do I need to know why?

941
01:38:19,236 --> 01:38:21,944
Nope. And neither does Bak.

942
01:38:24,111 --> 01:38:28,527
You're lucky Bak is an arsehole.
You'll have it in thirty.

943
01:39:28,820 --> 01:39:30,153
PREGNANT

944
01:39:31,820 --> 01:39:34,320
PREGNANT?

945
01:39:34,485 --> 01:39:37,735
Assad, we're going to Bornholm
to see Atu.

946
01:39:37,903 --> 01:39:41,944
- What about Rose?
- We need to get her out of there.

947
01:39:50,028 --> 01:39:55,778
Hi, June. It's Carl. I'm back.
I want to talk to you about some things.

948
01:39:55,944 --> 01:39:59,235
It appears Bjarke was part
of the sun cult.

949
01:39:59,403 --> 01:40:03,235
Do you know anything about that?

950
01:40:03,403 --> 01:40:07,985
I'm afraid Christian was right.
Bjarke was involved in Alberte's murder.

951
01:40:08,153 --> 01:40:11,902
Call me as soon as possible,
and I'll explain.

952
01:40:22,528 --> 01:40:24,778
Rose.

953
01:40:25,944 --> 01:40:28,277
You look happy?

954
01:40:28,445 --> 01:40:34,236
Atu took me for prayers
at the North Cliff. I can't describe it.

955
01:40:34,402 --> 01:40:38,569
- You don't have to. I know.
- Of course.

956
01:40:38,736 --> 01:40:44,819
I've actually spoken to Atu,
and we've decided you're ready.

957
01:40:44,986 --> 01:40:47,360
Ready for what?

958
01:40:48,903 --> 01:40:52,528
- For cleansing.
- Cleansing?

959
01:40:56,194 --> 01:40:59,735
Everyone must undergo
seven days of cleansing -

960
01:40:59,903 --> 01:41:02,444
- to be granted
permanent membership.

961
01:41:02,611 --> 01:41:05,861
- Seven days? That's a long time.
- Yes.

962
01:41:06,027 --> 01:41:10,527
You can ask Lola,
who's been in there for five days now.

963
01:41:18,153 --> 01:41:21,070
We take our shoes off in here.

964
01:41:24,860 --> 01:41:26,361
Holy shit.

965
01:41:26,527 --> 01:41:31,195
You sleep here, of course,
and the toilet's there.

966
01:41:31,360 --> 01:41:34,153
Damn, it's hot.

967
01:41:34,319 --> 01:41:36,319
So's the sun.

968
01:41:42,819 --> 01:41:47,486
- Who are you?
- Who am I? What do you mean?

969
01:41:48,736 --> 01:41:51,485
Are you police?

970
01:41:53,361 --> 01:41:55,777
No.

971
01:41:55,945 --> 01:41:58,652
I think you are.

972
01:42:00,402 --> 01:42:03,111
No, I'm not.

973
01:42:07,527 --> 01:42:10,735
I want to get out.

974
01:43:22,278 --> 01:43:25,235
I let myself in. I hope that's okay.

975
01:43:27,028 --> 01:43:28,902
Hi, Carl.

976
01:43:31,194 --> 01:43:36,110
I'm actually here to speak to Atu.
Or Frank, as he's really called.

977
01:43:36,278 --> 01:43:38,610
He's your brother, right?

978
01:43:38,778 --> 01:43:43,152
What happened?
You're bleeding.

979
01:43:45,986 --> 01:43:49,069
I was practising some karate.

980
01:43:49,236 --> 01:43:53,486
Frank had a relationship with Alberte,
didn't he? A sexual relationship?

981
01:43:53,652 --> 01:43:58,070
He has a sexual relationship
with nearly everyone here.

982
01:44:00,402 --> 01:44:03,444
Bjarke Habersaat.

983
01:44:03,611 --> 01:44:06,069
- Yes?
- What do you know about him?

984
01:44:06,236 --> 01:44:10,361
I first met him at a lecture
at the folk high school.

985
01:44:10,527 --> 01:44:17,110
He was curious, so he came to us.
We took him in and embraced him.

986
01:44:17,278 --> 01:44:22,610
Then he suddenly disappeared.
I heard he was living with his mum.

987
01:44:22,778 --> 01:44:27,236
He was special.
Very... his own.

988
01:44:27,402 --> 01:44:30,027
Unique.

989
01:44:39,485 --> 01:44:43,069
- That Frank, could I talk to him?
- His name is Atu.

990
01:44:43,236 --> 01:44:46,027
Can I talk to him?

991
01:44:49,360 --> 01:44:52,902
- Have you seen Rose?
- No.

992
01:44:57,195 --> 01:44:59,944
Have you seen Rose?

993
01:45:02,736 --> 01:45:04,736
Have you seen Rose?

994
01:45:04,902 --> 01:45:10,069
- Atu has an office down here.
- In the generator room? Okay.

995
01:45:10,236 --> 01:45:12,945
After you.

996
01:45:21,361 --> 01:45:24,485
Who knows you're here?

997
01:45:26,611 --> 01:45:31,778
- Hello? Who knows you're here?
- Rose. Only Rose.

998
01:45:32,860 --> 01:45:36,945
Rose isn't here anymore.
Who else knows?

999
01:45:37,110 --> 01:45:41,486
- What did you do to her?
- I haven't done anything.

1000
01:45:41,652 --> 01:45:47,986
I liked Rose. You sent her here.
It's your fault.

1001
01:45:48,152 --> 01:45:52,110
- Answer me. Who else knows?
- Did you kill her?

1002
01:45:52,278 --> 01:45:59,070
Did she get too close to your brother?
So she had to die? Like the others?

1003
01:45:59,235 --> 01:46:02,777
You're trivialising me,
and it's disrespectful.

1004
01:46:02,945 --> 01:46:05,653
The other girls were pregnant.

1005
01:46:05,819 --> 01:46:11,652
- Couldn't you become pregnant?
- Yes, I can become pregnant.

1006
01:46:11,820 --> 01:46:15,445
And only I can give birth to his child.

1007
01:46:21,236 --> 01:46:24,778
- Are you pregnant now?
- Yes, I am.

1008
01:46:24,944 --> 01:46:27,652
You're bleeding.

1009
01:46:46,527 --> 01:46:51,153
I can get you to the hospital.
Let me go.

1010
01:47:38,860 --> 01:47:40,320
Hello!

1011
01:47:49,277 --> 01:47:52,403
Have you seen Rose?

1012
01:48:14,277 --> 01:48:17,820
Carl?

1013
01:48:19,485 --> 01:48:21,653
Hey, Carl.
Can you hear me?

1014
01:48:21,819 --> 01:48:24,903
Hey, Carl! Carl, goddammit!

1015
01:48:25,069 --> 01:48:29,360
- Where is she? Pirjo, that bitch.
- She's up there.

1016
01:48:29,528 --> 01:48:34,235
I can't find Rose.
Up you go.

1017
01:48:34,403 --> 01:48:38,402
Easy, easy. Just a second.
Let me just... Ouch.

1018
01:49:27,778 --> 01:49:31,152
Lola? Lola!

1019
01:50:04,027 --> 01:50:06,236
Please. Come on.

1020
01:50:16,611 --> 01:50:19,277
Yes!

1021
01:50:27,361 --> 01:50:29,903
What's happened?

1022
01:50:31,110 --> 01:50:34,070
I lost her.

1023
01:50:35,569 --> 01:50:38,235
Forgive me.

1024
01:50:42,819 --> 01:50:45,861
Come sit with me.

1025
01:50:46,027 --> 01:50:48,111
Please.

1026
01:50:57,069 --> 01:51:00,195
I've always loved sitting here with you.

1027
01:51:06,736 --> 01:51:09,278
Police!

1028
01:51:11,528 --> 01:51:14,778
What's the police doing here?

1029
01:51:16,111 --> 01:51:20,653
- I think they know.
- Know what?

1030
01:51:22,444 --> 01:51:25,444
Everything.

1031
01:51:26,528 --> 01:51:30,111
I did it for your sake.

1032
01:51:30,277 --> 01:51:33,610
I did it for you.

1033
01:51:35,777 --> 01:51:39,278
I don't know what you're talking about.

1034
01:51:39,444 --> 01:51:42,153
This has nothing to do with me.

1035
01:51:42,319 --> 01:51:44,985
Don't go! Please.

1036
01:51:46,235 --> 01:51:48,695
Don't leave me.

1037
01:51:51,653 --> 01:51:57,277
Don't leave me. Don't leave me...

1038
01:52:11,319 --> 01:52:15,152
It's burning! It's burning!

1039
01:52:31,653 --> 01:52:35,027
She's dead. Come on.

1040
01:52:42,527 --> 01:52:45,028
Rose!

1041
01:53:08,820 --> 01:53:11,819
Rose?

1042
01:53:11,986 --> 01:53:14,069
Are you okay?

1043
01:53:14,236 --> 01:53:16,694
We can't find Atu.

1044
01:53:18,985 --> 01:53:21,445
I think I know where he is.

1045
01:54:08,361 --> 01:54:10,110
Atu!

1046
01:54:12,694 --> 01:54:17,403
Atu!
Stay away from the edge.

1047
01:54:17,569 --> 01:54:21,361
- Use me to drive out the darkness.
- Hey! Frank.

1048
01:54:22,986 --> 01:54:25,945
We have some questions
about Alberte Schneider.

1049
01:54:26,110 --> 01:54:28,360
Get away from the edge.

1050
01:54:28,528 --> 01:54:30,902
Light is strength.
Light is power.

1051
01:54:31,070 --> 01:54:33,403
Carl?

1052
01:54:37,570 --> 01:54:40,360
Stay on him.

1053
01:54:41,402 --> 01:54:46,111
Don't you dare accuse Bjarke
like Christian did.

1054
01:54:46,277 --> 01:54:50,320
My son isn't a murderer.
Don't you get it? They used him -

1055
01:54:50,485 --> 01:54:53,861
- because he loved them.
Because for the first time -

1056
01:54:54,027 --> 01:54:57,820
- he felt like he belonged somewhere.

1057
01:54:59,820 --> 01:55:02,653
For Christ's sake, June.

1058
01:55:02,819 --> 01:55:08,820
Bjarke came out to me one evening.
He was completely beside himself.

1059
01:55:08,985 --> 01:55:13,153
Alberte was a threat to the cult
because she was pregnant.

1060
01:55:13,319 --> 01:55:16,403
- Said who?
- The sister.

1061
01:55:16,569 --> 01:55:18,903
She did the talking.

1062
01:55:19,069 --> 01:55:24,319
But he, the Sun King,
knows everything.

1063
01:55:24,486 --> 01:55:28,527
Bjarke was afraid,
but he also felt chosen.

1064
01:55:28,695 --> 01:55:31,653
They had such power over him.

1065
01:55:31,819 --> 01:55:35,820
I tried to calm him down,
but I couldn't reach him.

1066
01:55:36,820 --> 01:55:42,569
The next morning,
I drove out here to speak to Atu.

1067
01:55:42,736 --> 01:55:47,861
I just wanted to talk.
And then I see her -

1068
01:55:48,027 --> 01:55:50,444
- and there's no one else around.

1069
01:55:52,736 --> 01:55:57,152
It was just an impulse.
It was so easy, it happened so fast.

1070
01:56:06,985 --> 01:56:12,361
I just wanted Bjarke
to continue being happy.

1071
01:56:12,527 --> 01:56:15,444
I did it for our son.

1072
01:56:17,777 --> 01:56:23,652
But they kicked him out anyway.
Atu said the sun didn't want him.

1073
01:56:23,819 --> 01:56:26,736
That's why he started taking drugs again.

1074
01:56:26,902 --> 01:56:30,694
He was so lonely.

1075
01:56:30,861 --> 01:56:35,736
June, get in the car, and stay there.

1076
01:56:39,028 --> 01:56:42,278
Yes.

1077
01:58:04,320 --> 01:58:09,027
- June? Call an ambulance.
- She needs to be cut out, Carl.

1078
01:58:09,195 --> 01:58:12,195
Copenhagen Police.
There's been a crash...

1079
01:58:12,360 --> 01:58:15,235
Carl.

1080
01:58:20,402 --> 01:58:22,735
Carl, we need to leave.

1081
01:58:23,778 --> 01:58:27,527
- I'm sorry, June.
- Move!

1082
01:59:29,320 --> 01:59:32,903
- Hi.
- Hi.

1083
01:59:54,527 --> 01:59:57,444
- Hi, Gordon.
- Hi.

1084
01:59:57,611 --> 01:59:59,652
Hello, Gordon.

1085
01:59:59,820 --> 02:00:04,277
It's all coming down.
And the boxes go in the basement.

1086
02:00:09,819 --> 02:00:11,819
Rose?

1087
02:00:11,986 --> 02:00:13,652
You okay?

1088
02:00:17,652 --> 02:00:20,277
Yes.
